                "style": "",
                "text": "Ohio Quietly Passes A Bill That Could Bankrupt Churches Linked To Fossil Fuel Protests",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.huffpost.com/entry/ohio-fossil-fuel_n_5fdb862cc5b6f24ae35e61ba",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " (Huffington Post) — ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "“Ohio lawmakers faced fierce blowback last winter over a bill that would escalate criminal charges on fossil fuel protesters and threaten religious organizations or nonprofits that support such demonstrations with crushing fines…For nearly a year, the bill sat dormant. But this week, on the state Legislature’s final day, House lawmakers quietly passed it.”",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
